`@motion-core/motion-gpu` is a Svelte 5 runtime for fullscreen WGSL rendering on WebGPU.

This documentation was rebuilt directly from `packages/motion-gpu/src` and its test suite, so all contracts below reflect real implementation behavior, defaults, and failure modes.

## What this package actually ships

| Area | Source of truth | Notes |
| --- | --- | --- |
| Runtime component | `src/lib/FragCanvas.svelte` | Owns canvas, renderer lifecycle, scheduler integration, and error overlay. |
| Material pipeline | `src/lib/core/material.ts` + `material-preprocess.ts` | Validates fragment contract, expands includes/defines, computes deterministic signatures. |
| Renderer | `src/lib/core/renderer.ts` | WebGPU setup, shader compile checks, uniform writes, texture uploads, pass execution. |
| Scheduler | `src/lib/frame-context.ts` | Ordered frame tasks, stage graph, invalidation, render modes, diagnostics/profiling. |
| Pass system | `src/lib/core/render-graph.ts` + `src/lib/passes/*` | Ping-pong source/target model and optional canvas output. |
| Texture loading | `src/lib/core/texture-loader.ts` + `use-texture.ts` | URL decode, cancellation, caching, reactive hook state. |
| Diagnostics | `src/lib/core/error-report.ts` | Maps low-level runtime errors to structured reports with hints. |

## Public entrypoints

| Entrypoint | Exports |
| --- | --- |
| `@motion-core/motion-gpu` | `FragCanvas`, `defineMaterial`, `useMotionGPU`, `useFrame`, `useTexture`, `BlitPass`, `CopyPass`, `ShaderPass` |
| `@motion-core/motion-gpu/advanced` | Everything above plus `useMotionGPUUserContext` and advanced scheduler/user-context types |

The export contract is verified in tests (`src/tests/public-api.test.ts`).

## Runtime mental model

1. You create an immutable material with `defineMaterial(...)`.
2. `FragCanvas` resolves that material and derives a renderer pipeline signature.
3. If signature changes, renderer is rebuilt (with retry backoff on init failures).
4. Every animation frame:
   - scheduler tasks run (`useFrame` registrations),
   - runtime uniforms/textures are merged,
   - fullscreen base pass renders,
   - optional post-process passes execute,
   - final result is presented to canvas.

## Technical contracts you should treat as hard requirements

| Contract | Enforced by |
| --- | --- |
| Fragment function signature must be `fn frag(uv: vec2f) -> vec4f` | `defineMaterial` validation |
| `ShaderPass` fragment must define `fn shade(inputColor: vec4f, uv: vec2f) -> vec4f` | `ShaderPass` constructor |
| Uniform / texture keys must be WGSL-safe identifiers (`[A-Za-z_][A-Za-z0-9_]*`) | uniform + texture validators |
| `renderMode` can only be `always`, `on-demand`, `manual` | scheduler runtime |
| `maxDelta > 0`, `profilingWindow > 0` | scheduler assertions |
| Render target dimensions and scale must be finite and > 0 | render-target resolver |

## Defaults worth knowing

| Setting | Default |
| --- | --- |
| `FragCanvas.clearColor` | `[0, 0, 0, 1]` |
| `FragCanvas.outputColorSpace` | `'srgb'` |
| `FragCanvas.renderMode` | `'always'` |
| `FragCanvas.autoRender` | `true` |
| `FragCanvas.maxDelta` | `0.1` |
| Texture filter | `'linear'` |
| Texture address mode | `'clamp-to-edge'` |
| Texture update mode | source-dependent (`video -> perFrame`, otherwise `once`) |

